<div class="wiki-item">
	<h3 class="title"><a class="" href="/wiki/237/force-a-user-to-change-their-password-changepasswordfilter/">Force a User to Change Their Password (ChangePasswordFilter)</a></h3>
    <div class="teaser">
        <div class="info">
                        Created 3 years ago            by <a class="g-user-rank-link" href="/user/4657/">waterloomatt</a>                                &ndash; <a href="/wiki/?category=3">Tutorials</a>            		&ndash; <a href="/wiki/237/force-a-user-to-change-their-password-changepasswordfilter/#comments">2 comments</a>    		&ndash; viewed 14,880 times
                    &ndash;
            ( <span class="g-vote plus" title="16 votes up">+16</span> / <span class="g-vote minus" title="2 votes down">-2</span> )
                            &ndash;
            version <strong>1.1</strong>
                </div>
        Sometimes you need to force a user to change their password after x number of days. This article describes how to implement this using a filter, ChangePasswordFilter.                    <div class="tags">
                <strong>tags:</strong>
                <a href="/wiki/?tag=security">security</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filters">filters</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=password">password</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=user+management">user management</a>            </div>
